  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge build\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (M1)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nfollowing [the tutorial](https://book.getfoundry.sh/projects/working-on-an-existing-project.html), however not matter how many times I've built the project, `forge` will still take time to install `solc`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n➜  forge-std git:(master) ✗ forge build\r\n[⠒] Compiling...\r\n[⠢] installing solc version \"0.8.10\"\r\n[⠔] Successfully installed solc 0.8.10\r\nNo files changed, compilation skipped\r\n➜  forge-std git:(master) ✗ forge build\r\n[⠊] Compiling...\r\n[⠰] installing solc version \"0.8.10\"\r\n[⠑] Successfully installed solc 0.8.10\r\nNo files changed, compilation skipped\r\n```\r\n\r\nfrom my understanding `solc` should only be installed once, am I correct?",
